olive oil
2 potato
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
1 stalk celery
3 clove garlic
1 bag thyme
1 packet Chicken Drumstick Fillet
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
¼ tsp salt
1 packet diced bacon
½ packet cream
1 sachet beef-style stock powder

• Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to the
boil.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks. Thinly
slice onion. Thinly slice carrot into half-moons.
Finely chop celery and garlic. Pick thyme
leaves.
• Cut boneless chicken drumsticks into 2cm
chunks.

• Cook potato in the boiling water until easily
pierced with a fork, 10-15 minutes. Drain and
return potato to the saucepan.
• Add the butter, milk and the salt, then mash
until smooth.

Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help
mash the potatoes!

• While the potato is cooking, heat a large frying
pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of
olive oil. When oil hot, cook chicken until
browned, 5-6 minutes. Transfer to a bowl.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil. Cook diced bacon, breaking up with
a spoon, until golden, 6-7 minutes.
• Add onion, carrot and celery. Cook, stirring,
until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic and thyme and cook until fragrant,
1 minute.

• Reduce heat to low, then add cream (see ingredients) and beef-style stock powder. Cook, stirring, until thickened, 1-2 minutes.
• Return chicken to the pan and stir to combine. Season to taste.

• Preheat the grill to high. Transfer the filling to a
baking dish, then top with the mashed potato.
• Run a fork over the mash to create an uneven
surface. Grill pie until browned, 6-10 minutes.

Little cooks: Join in on the fun by smoothing the
mash mixture evenly over the pie!

• Divide chicken, bacon and thyme pie between
plates. Enjoy!